{{/*
  p28.18 ONE reusable date-input component. Dot is a dateFieldModel (built by the
  `datefield` template func, render.go). Every date text input on every page renders
  through THIS partial so the markup — canonical `input.js-datefield` that the global
  enhancer (static/datefield.js) wires with parse/format, GnuCash shortcuts, and the
  calendar popover — is defined once, not recreated per site (owner directive).

  Canonical, always emitted: type="text", the `js-datefield` hook class (plus any
  caller Class), and autocomplete="off" (rule 10/12 — never input[type=date]; the
  server, money.ParseDate, is the parse authority). Optional attributes are OMITTED
  when their field is empty (name/value/placeholder/data-date-format), so a site that
  wrote none by hand reproduces exactly. Autofocus is a caller-computed error flag.
*/ -}}
{{- define "datefield" -}}
<input type="text" id="{{.ID}}"{{if .Name}} name="{{.Name}}"{{end}} class="js-datefield{{if .Class}} {{.Class}}{{end}}"{{if .Value}} value="{{.Value}}"{{end}}{{if .Placeholder}} placeholder="{{.Placeholder}}"{{end}}{{if .Format}} data-date-format="{{.Format}}"{{end}} autocomplete="off"{{if .Autofocus}} autofocus{{end}}>
{{- end -}}
